She flipped to an empty page and noted the date. Below that, she wrote "11.5.648–13.12.648".
"Are you refreshing old memories?" Ivory inquired and looked at the old notebook. Kari nodded. "Do you think they'll let you out for Christmas? After all, it's only a few days away."
Kari knocked twice on the lantern. "No," as Ivory had suspected. The Ice King never let Kari out, as he considered her a "blemish." She was born deaf and was the only daughter in the family; her siblings were all boys.
Similar things happened to Ivory as well. When Ivory came out as non-binary, it seemed as though the world was changing around them. As punishment for this difference, Ivory was given tasks where they would mostly be alone.
Moreover, Ivory was also forced to serve the princess. However, this did not bother Ivory much, as she gained a friend in the process.
"You have a birthday coming up soon, right?" Ivory asked, remembering that the princess had her birthday in a few days. Kari nodded with a sad glimmer in her blue eyes.
"Would you like to celebrate your birthday?" Ivory asked, thinking about the last time the princess had answered this question.
"No," Kari knocked. Ivory knew this was a difficult topic for her. Her birthday was the day she was locked in this room and her mother was banished. At that time, Ivory had been a baby, but she remembered how upset the servants and the city's residents were. Ivory had heard that Eirwen was a popular queen who could also apparently predict things that would later come true.
"Now, what do you want to do?" asked Ivory. Kari looked excitedly at Ivory and held a piece of paper in her hand. It read:
The translation of "15 x 15 cm Leinwand" from German to English is:  "15 x 15 cm canvas"  This refers to a piece of canvas that measures 15 centimeters by 15 centimeters.
The translation of "Weiß, verschiedene Blautöne" from German to English is:  "White, various shades of blue"
Brushes in six different sizes
The German word "Staffelei" translates to " easel" in English.
"Should I get these things for you?" Ivory asked the silent princess, whose braids swung back and forth due to her vigorous knocking. "Yes?" Ivory giggled softly. The usually reserved princess showed such enthusiasm. It was the first time she had asked for something that wasn't related to books and came from outside her room.
"Okay! See you later?" Ivory asked, stood up, and wove her way through the chaos of papers and notebooks.
Kari nodded, turned back to her notes, and wrapped herself in her blanket.
Ivory left the room, relieved that the princess finally stepped out of her comfort zone and asked for things outside her reach, like Malfarben.
Ivory wandered through the hallways again and tried to ignore the gossip of the maids.
"I have heard that she is said to be possessed by Queen Eirwen and therefore keeps going into that room."
"I have heard that they eat children in this room."
"She looks like a man, that's not normal, is it?"
Ivory held her ears, unable to ignore the chatter, and continued on. The room of the royal painter was in the east wing, behind the second door on the left side.
Ivory approached the door, which was just as intricately adorned as Karis's door. On it was the White Dragon, one of the six Urdragons allegedly created by Frostfall. For an art historian, the presence of the White Dragon on the door made perfect sense.
Ivory opened the door and expected the usual chaos. Splashes of paint everywhere, brushes and papers scattered throughout the room, and canvases covering every inch of the wall. Surprisingly, however, a different sight greeted her. The entire room was clean, and in front of a red velvet background stood a chair. On the chair sat Kronprinz Aquilo, who was being portraitured.
"Good morning, Ivory! Would you like to watch as your future king is portraited?" Aquilo asked and winked at Ivory.
"Sorry, Little Prince," said Ivory, largely ignoring him and gathering together the things that the quiet Princess wished for. "I'm only here to get Mal's things."
"Is my little girl ready to go already?" asked Aquilo. "But I want you to stay!"
"but not me," Ivory found the painting supplies on the list and put them in a box. "Besides, I'm not a girl."
The prince, however, had a different opinion. "Oh sweetie, this is just a phase! As you get older, you'll grow out of it!" he said vaguely.
"I have to go," said Ivory, feeling uncomfortable with the prince's response. At that moment, Ivory remembered all the ugly remarks he and others had made about his gender identity in the past. I just want to get out of here.
"Are you leaving already?" Suddenly, the prince appeared at the door and ignored the loud objections of the royal painter.
"It is not behavior for a future king!" said Ivory.
"Nobody will find out. People won't believe you, and the painter will keep quiet if his life means anything to him." He looked at the painter briefly and then leaned closer towards Ivory. "What do you think about a date?" Ivory had been harassed multiple times in the past, but never by a prince, let alone the crown prince.
"Do you actually know what the word 'No' means?" Ivory spat out and pushed the crown prince away from her.
"No," Aquilo replied with a smile. Of course, the crown prince, who can have anything he wants, doesn't know what the word 'no' means.
Ivory rolled her eyes. "Why do you want to go out with someone like me? You must have around 100 admirers?"
"Actually, it's 50," he interrupted Ivory, still smiling. He threw back his hair, which whipped around in the cold air.
"Now get it straight! Why me? I am a threat to the palace." Ivory crossed her arms.
"You are the most beautiful girl I have ever seen." Aquilo raised Ivory's chin with his finger and forced Ivory to look at him.
